
**Linux Filesystem Hierarchy**

/ ---> top most directory in linux
  ---> everything is mounted under /
  

  windows                                                Linux

  C:\                                                     /

  configuration files stored in                          /etc
  C:\windows

  home directory for user                                /home
  C:\users

  all installed application/software                     /usr  (Unix System Resource)
  files stored in 
  C:\program files                                        OR

                                                         /opt

 temporary files stored in
 C:\temp                                                 /tmp

 /root : home directory for root user
 /boot : It contains all boot loader files
 POST method : Power On Self Test
 /dev : (device) all essencial device file information stored here
 /var : (Variable data) : store system logs 
 /media : mounted point for for removable media
 /mnt : mounted directory for file